==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: environmental
<hw>environmental</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of or pertaining
to the environment; <as>as, <ex>environmental</ex>
factors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>of or pertaining to the environment (definition 2);
<as>as, <ex>environmental</ex> pollution; <ex>environmental</ex>
disaster; <ex>environmental</ex> cleanup; <ex>environmental</ex>
deterioration</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><q>THOUSANDS of dead fish and other marine species, suffocated by a
rotting, glutinous morass which spreads over kilometres of coral
reefs.⟦br⟧
This scenario has all the hallmarks of a unnatural
<qex>environmental</qex> disaster resulting from
<qex>environmental</qex> negligence. However this isn't the case,
instead the cause -- coral spawn slick deoxygenation -- is a natural
event which has the potential to occur periodically on the reefs of the
West Pilbara.</q> <rj><qau>Michael Borowitzka (⟦ldquo⟧Natural event
spawns environmental disaster⟦rdquo⟧ in Murdoch News, October 12,
1995)</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Environs</ent>⟦br⟧
